Package makesudokus.logic.algorithms.crook

Class PreemptiveSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • makesudokus.logic.algorithms.crook.PreemptiveSet
  • public class PreemptiveSet
extends java.lang.Object
    A preemptive set is a tuple of small lists shaped like {[1,2,6], [c(1,7), c(1,9), c(2,9)]} (example from Crook's paper. The first list contains markups (the markups make up the span of the set) and the second one the cells where said markups are found within a related area (3x3 box, row, column) and it's length is called size.
